defconfig (linux, based on arm-unknown-linux-gnueabi):

```
CT_CONFIG_VERSION="4"
CT_OBSOLETE=y # Necessary for all available options
CT_DEBUG_CT=y # Necessary to save steps
CT_DEBUG_CT_SAVE_STEPS=y # Saves each compilation steps to continue from. CONTINUE= and STOP= is useful to do a re-build-and-error loop.
# CT_REMOVE_DOCS is not set
CT_STRIP_TARGET_TOOLCHAIN_EXECUTABLES=y # I don't know why it's enabled, but better to have a smaller toolchain to redistribute
CT_ARCH_ARM=y
CT_ARCH_FLOAT_SW=y # For armel (gnueabi), say y. for armhf (gnueabihf), say n. Mutually exclusive to CT_ARCH_FLOAT_HW.
CT_ARCH_FLOAT_HW=y # For armel (gnueabi), say n. for armhf (gnueabihf), say y. Mutually exclusive to CT_ARCH_FLOAT_SW.
CT_STATIC_TOOLCHAIN=y # Prefer smaller size
CT_KERNEL_LINUX=y
CT_LINUX_V_4_15=y # Specify the matching version to the Ubuntu LTS
CT_BINUTILS_V_2_26=y # Specify the matching version to the Ubuntu LTS
CT_GLIBC_V_2_23=y # Specify the matching version to the Ubuntu LTS
CT_GLIBC_EXTRA_CFLAGS="-Wno-missing-attributes -Wno-array-bounds -Wno-array-parameter -Wno-stringop-overflow -Wno-maybe-uninitialized -Wno-implicit-int"
CT_GLIBC_ENABLE_COMMON_FLAG=y
CT_GCC_V_5=y # Specify the matching version to the Ubuntu LTS
# CT_CC_GCC_SJLJ_EXCEPTIONS is not set
CT_CC_LANG_CXX=y
CT_DEBUG_DUMA=y
CT_DEBUG_GDB=y
CT_GDB_NATIVE=y
CT_DEBUG_LTRACE=y
CT_DEBUG_STRACE=y
CT_GMP_V_6_1=y # Specify the matching version to the Ubuntu LTS
CT_GMP_EXTRA_CFLAGS="-std=gnu17"
CT_ISL_V_0_15=y # Specify the matching version to the Ubuntu LTS
CT_NCURSES_EXTRA_CFLAGS="-std=gnu11" # GCC 5 will not understand gnu17 but gnu11
CT_ZSTD_NEEDED=y
```

defconfig (bare-metal, based on samples/arm-none-eabi):
