# Proposed plan toward the finish

Here I propose an example of steps to implement all the requirements.
Start plan mode to elaborate it.

- Ensure ct-ng 1.28.0 (or 1.22.0) fulfills the each combination of versions of each LTSes.
   - For 1.28.0, `/packages` directory contains all possible versions of all deps.
   - For 1.22.0, `/config` directory contains *.in files that contains all possible versions.
   - If 1.22.0 is not suitable to build older versions, report me about that, re-search other versions, and suggest the better ct-ng version.
- Start from newer Ubuntu LTS, create config, edit it, build-and-error it, and savedefconfig it.
   - On building ct-ng itself, configure it with `./configure --enable-local` to contain the ct-ng binary inside in the repo
   - If any patch to ct-ng, like changing URLs, do it as needed.
   - When building, redirect stdout to /dev/null to decrease the token use. You can check if it succeeded by reading $? and you can read the log by opening `build.log`.
- Move the defconfig to corresponding dir and commit it.
   - For Linux targets: `arm-unknown-linux-gnueabi(hf)?-uXXYY` (e.g. arm-unknown-linux-gnueabi-u2404)
   - For bare-metal targets: `arm-none-eabi-uXXYY` (e.g. arm-none-eabi-u2404)
- Compress the context of you to keep going without losing info about GH Action later on.
- Read the existing GH Actions workflow from upstream and understand what to do to create archives.
- Reuse or rewrite GH Actions workflow to build and upload all combinations of proposed matrix.
   - Specify CT_PREFIX `/opt/x-tools` as the prefix on build with environment variable. Necessary on host machine.
- Try running the workflow, watch it with gh CLI, and do try-and-error loop until the ultimate success.
   - Try decreasing waiting time while testing builds on GH Actions. Every second matters.

